---
title: One-Pan Spiced Chicken & Cauliflower Rice with Golden Raisins, Carrots & Cilantro Yogurt Sauce
description: Tonight’s spiced chicken has all the typical Middle Eastern-inspired flavors of shawarma, but it’s cooked in one pan. You’ll add carrots, garlic, rice, and raisins to your chicken, then mix it all together with a squeeze of fresh lemon, a drizzle of cilantro crema, and a garnish of almonds. It all adds up to a dinner that’s easy to clean up and even easier to gobble down.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62f3d81a71b75adab70ba1c8-856ac601.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-spiced-chicken-cauliflower-rice-62f3d81a71b75adab70ba1c8-5cc84db6.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-spiced-chicken-cauliflower-rice-62f3d81a71b75adab70ba1c8
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 510 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 48 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 940 mg
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Middle East
---

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @Shawarma spice blend{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Shawarma Spice Blend later.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a medium, preferably #nonstick pan{} (use a large, preferably nonstick, pan for 4) over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer chicken to a #plate{}; reserve pan.

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and dice @carrots{9%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add carrots in a single layer; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan with carrots; add garlic, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, remaining Shawarma Spice Blend, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @water{1 1/2%cups}, @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, and @chicken stock concentrate{2}. Bring to a boil; cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}. Cover pan and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if mixture seems dry.

Remove pan from heat; return chicken to pan. Let stand to warm through, ~{3%minutes}.

> After cooking garlic and raisins, add cauliflower rice (no need to drain), stock concentrates, a big pinch of salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 6-8 minutes. Follow the rest of this step as instructed. (Save jasmine rice for another use.)

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, and half the cilantro. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; slice crosswise.

Fluff rice mixture with a #fork{} and stir in a big squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Divide rice mixture between #bowls{}. Top with chicken and garnish with @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and remaining cilantro. Drizzle with sauce. Squeeze juice from any remaining lemon wedges over bowls to taste. Serve.